      "text": "  Let  $H$  be a complex Hilbert space of dimension not less than 3. For every positive integer  $k < \\dim H$  we denote by  $\\mathcal{G}_k(H)$  and  $\\mathcal{G}^k(H)$  the Grassmannians formed by  $k$ -dimensional subspaces of  $H$  and closed subspaces of  $H$  whose codimension is  $k$ , respectively. Note that  $\\mathcal{G}^k(H) = \\mathcal{G}_{n-k}(H)$  if dim  $H = n$  is finite. In the case when H is infinite-dimensional, we write  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$  for the Grassmannian of closed subspaces of  $H$  whose dimension and codimension both are infinite.",
      "line_with_spans": [
        {
          "category_type": "text_span",
          "poly": [
            517.5,
