      "text": "  Let  $\\mathcal{G}$  be one of the Grassmannians  $\\mathcal{G}_k(H)$ ,  $\\mathcal{G}^k(H)$  or  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$ .Elements  $X, Y \\in \\mathcal{G}$  are called *adjacent* if  $X \\cap Y$  is a hyperplane in both  $X, Y$ . In the case when  $\\mathcal{G}$  is  $\\mathcal{G}_1(H)$  or  $\\mathcal{G}^1(H)$ , any two distinct elements of  $\\mathcal{G}$  are adjacent. Recall that two closed subspaces of  $H$  are *compatible* if there is an orthonormal basis of  $H$  such that each of these subspaces is spanned by a subset of this basis. We say that  $X, Y \\in \\mathcal{G}$  are *ortho-adjacent* if they are adjacent and compatible.",
