      "anno_id": 1,
      "text": " Every unitary or anti-unitary operator on  $H$  induces bijective transformations of  $\\mathcal{G}_k(H), \\mathcal{G}^k(H)$  and  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$  which preserve the ortho-adjacency relation in both directions. The orthocomplementary map  $X \\to X^{\\bot}$  is a bijection of  $\\mathcal{G}_k(H)$  to  $\\mathcal{G}^k(H)$  and a bijective transformation of  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$  preserving the ortho-adjacency in both directions.",
